WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.293
Previously on The Originals...

00:01.293 --> 00:03.387
A thousand years ago, we three made

00:03.390 --> 00:05.571
an eternal vow. Always and forever.

00:05.574 --> 00:07.813
- That vow now includes my daughter.
- Hope's gone.

00:07.814 --> 00:09.007
She's the Hollow now.

00:09.010 --> 00:10.470
You said there was a way to save her.

00:10.472 --> 00:12.312
There is. When the Hollow was killed,

00:12.315 --> 00:15.145
they divided her remains.
Four bones, four volunteers,

00:15.148 --> 00:16.350
four different locations.

00:16.352 --> 00:18.218
That's how we're going
to beat the Hollow now.

00:18.220 --> 00:20.640
Transfer the Hollow's power
into four immortal vampires.

00:20.643 --> 00:22.421
And you have to go your separate ways,

00:22.424 --> 00:25.164
and you have to stay separate.
Can never see each other again.

00:25.167 --> 00:26.754
Can never go near each other again.

00:26.757 --> 00:29.254
This is gonna be tbe end
of always and forever.

00:29.257 --> 00:32.031
Well, if it'll save my little
girl, then we will make it so.

00:32.034 --> 00:34.134
When this spell is
over, you got to get away

00:34.136 --> 00:35.703
from each other, and
you have to stay away.

00:35.705 --> 00:37.554
I can hear it whispering.

00:37.557 --> 00:39.390
Caroline and I have built a school.

00:39.393 --> 00:41.559
It's a place for kids
with supernatural leanings,

00:41.562 --> 00:42.609
just like Hope.

00:42.611 --> 00:44.473
I think this is what
she's always wanted.

00:44.476 --> 00:46.004
Friends her own age.

00:46.007 --> 00:47.367
A normal life.

00:48.484 --> 00:49.950
My disease has always been

00:49.952 --> 00:51.718
blind devotion to my brother

00:51.720 --> 00:53.263
The Hollow's too
powerful. It's gonna tempt

00:53.265 --> 00:54.721
him to try to get
back with his siblings.

00:54.723 --> 00:55.687
Compel me.

00:55.690 --> 00:58.156
We can wipe out
centuries of family drama.

00:58.159 --> 00:59.872
The promise of always and forever.

00:59.875 --> 01:01.094
Forget it.

01:04.340 --> 01:05.640
Your vow.

01:05.643 --> 01:08.043
Let it go.

01:09.007 --> 01:11.881
_

01:12.335 --> 01:14.341
In all my travels,

01:14.343 --> 01:16.743
France never disappoints.

01:16.745 --> 01:20.080
Now I find I'm physically
drawn to the place,

01:20.082 --> 01:23.917
as if locked in an orbit
I'm helpless to alter.

01:23.920 --> 01:27.557
I suppose we're all satellites

01:27.560 --> 01:30.057
orbiting those we love.

01:30.059 --> 01:34.061
Recently, though, I'm
left to orbit from afar,

01:34.063 --> 01:35.662
and to pass the time

01:35.664 --> 01:37.479
by dropping in on old acquaintances.

01:37.482 --> 01:39.448
Entres nous, in 1928,

01:39.451 --> 01:43.169
the Gatineaux family and
I had a little falling out.

01:43.172 --> 01:45.772
I'd really like to put that to rest.

01:45.774 --> 01:48.742
So if you'll just... stand aside?

01:50.980 --> 01:52.412
You must've heard of me.

01:52.414 --> 01:54.147
Klaus le Fou?

01:54.149 --> 01:56.049
Klaus le Dement?

01:56.051 --> 01:58.652
Niklaus der Morder?

01:58.654 --> 02:00.287
No?

02:00.289 --> 02:02.556
Nothing?

